commitResults.messageBody:
Checkstyle errors were introduced during GUI development.
These were fixed, and JavaDocs were added or updated for the modified classes.

During development, StackOverflow snippets were used a few times without attribution,
these were fixed by adding a comment stating the author's name, date the answer was written,
and a link to the answer along with the name of the license under which the answer is provided.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix licenses, add details about SE-EDU website licensing
Use assertions to document assumptions in code
commitResults.messageBody:
Important assumptions during code execution, such as list indices being less than the
length of the list and not being negative have been documented.

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve code quality by deleting TODO comments, renaming variables
commitResults.messageBody:
Delete old TODO comments that were used in development. I renamed constant variables using snake case
and changed their access modifier to private static. I also added some comments explaining the main
Duke code which could potentially trip up someone reading the code base, such as the CommandEventListener
and InputEventListener.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add deadline sorting functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadlines have a natural ordering, sorted by when they are due. When the user types "sort",
the SortDeadlinesCommand finds all the deadlines in the task list, and sorts them by when they are due,
then renders this to the view.
